race.comment: KAFFIR LILY (11) switched from the Archibald yard and looked a run short resuming at the Sunshine Coast. She's raced at Group level and is suited stepping up to the mile. Maps well and has plenty up here sleeve. SMART ACTION (7) has been racing in stronger company and is much better than the form line suggests. He was only beaten 2.6L here in a 90 last time over this distance and that stacks right up. Has an inside barrier and handy 2kg claim. KIND WISH (8) wasn't far away at Eagle Farm in a CL5 and this is much easier. She can use the inside gate and Thompson replaces Bayliss who rides the top selection. HEREDITARY (4) brings good form from the Sunshine Coast and benefits from a 3kg claim today. Comes back a touch in trip and value chance.
